The paper discusses the mechanism design and analysis of sponsored search mechanisms, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves modeling the interaction of publishers, advertisers, and end-users, which can be categorized under information retrieval (cs.IR) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also analyzes the strategic behaviors of end-users and advertisers, which can be categorized under multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and economics (cs.EC).
